args: So this is where Surtr was freed from the\nmimicry. It's hard to imagine, given how\nthe place appears now.
The reconstruction of Grams proceeds\nsimilarly apace. Humans certainly do\nhave that indomitable-spirit thing down.
Well, lookee who's here! What are you two\nso deep in thought over, mmm?
Merely chatting about how good this area\nlooks even though it was the sight of a\ngrand battle with a demon.
Yeah, that was a heck of a time, all right.\nAnd on that note...
I seem to recall promising to give you a\nright thumping, so let's get it over with.
I think you got in plenty of thumps\nwhen we fought back in Grams.
But that was then, and this is not then!\nJust THINKING about the way you acted\nmakes me furious! You're ALWAYSâ€”
Stow the chatter. We have a mission\nto complete.
Fine, fine. But I'm not gonna forget that\nthumping, Michael!
I am in no position to say this, but...\nI hope you rest in peace.
Yes! This time we got the KO!
Wait. There's something off about him...
What...what am I doing...? Ah, of course.\nThis is the ebb before the great wave.
Enough with the mumbling! If you still\nwanna fight, hurry up and do it already.
Nnngh... Let us talk about the demon\ninside me while I am still myself.
The demon within me is called Surtr.\nHe is a calamity clad in furious flame\nwho lacks the tongue to speak.
His thoughts and desires are utterly\nincomprehensible to me. All I know for\ncertain is that he seeks his own demise.
You're not exactly winning orator of the\nyear awards yourself here, buddy.
Easy, Raphael. Let's hear him out.
Surtr's longing for death manifests as a\nmiasma that flows from him and robs all\naround him of beliefâ€”including myself.
Belief is a guiding principle for the self,\nand to lose sight of it is to lose the will to\nlive itself andâ€”AAAAH!
Look at that miasma! This must be the\npower of the demon he's talking about.
I can't...I can't control it! Hunger! Thirst!\nThey consume me! I must release this\nanguish! I MUST RELEASE IT!
This demon...cannot be loosed upon the\nworld... You must stop me... PLEASE!
It's been so hard, so painful...\nBut I feel nothing...I don't understand...\nI...I...AAAAAAAAAAH!
If it hurts so badly, release the demon\nand end your suffering.
Michael! What are you doing here?!
I'm not here to cause trouble, I promise.\nAlthough I'm not here to HELP either...
What is your goal in all of this, then?!
My goal? Simple. I seek to help Basileus,\nas any parent would support their child.
That belief is the lodestar of my existence.\nI cannot surrender it, no matter what.
But as I said earlier, I am not your enemy\nat the present time. Your enemy is right\nover there.
Death approaches... I'll be eaten!\nEaten away! End this boredom!\nAAAH HA HA HA HA HA!

So what was all that bit about ï¼‚don't take
my words to have a hidden meaningï¼‚?!
Ugh, I am going to give you a right
thumping the next time I see you!

Do as you will. If you think of me as an
enemy, you can pummel me to your
heart's contentâ€”though I suggest waiting
until after this particular storm.
I pray for your good health. Farewell.
Rrrgh! I can't stand how he's always\nall condescending and calm and junk!\nHe's ALWAYS been like that!
I hear you, but right now, we need to focus\non the enemy in front of us.
Agreed. Let us bring peace to our poor\ncomrade's soul and end his suffering.\nSigil, release!
Oh, I'm ready. We'll send him and that\ndemon to the next world!
